The paper describes a robotics competition that involves domestic tasks requiring autonomous capabilities, which suggests a focus on robotics and automation (cs.RO). The competition also involves a large variety of AI technologies, indicating a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses human-robot interaction (cs.HC) and the integration of subsystems into a fully functional system, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV).
